title: Readout of the President's call with King Abdullah of Jordan | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House
Office of the Press Secretary


For Immediate Release
February 01, 2010

 



Readout of the President's call with King Abdullah of Jordan




The President and King Abdullah spoke this morning about efforts to get Israeli-Palestinian negotiations underway and Special Envoy Mitchell’s latest trip to the region. They also discussed several areas of mutual interest. The President expressed his appreciation for Jordan’s staunch support for a two-state solution and comprehensive peace in the region, and told the King he considers Jordan to be an integral partner of the United States.
